The NPA has issued a summons to Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan. JOHANNESBURG - National Prosecuting Authority head Shaun Abrahams has announced that a summons has been issued to Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan relating to a fraud charge. Summons have been issued for Gordhan, former Sars commissioner Oupa Magashula and former deputy Sars Commissioner Ivan Pillay. It's believe the charge of fraud relates to the payout made by Sars to Pillay when he took early retirement. WATCH: The NPA briefing  